---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Paringkelan - Balinese Calendar" description="Understanding Paringkelan systems in the Balinese calendar">
	<h1 class="font-display text-4xl gold-accent mb-8">Paringkelan</h1>

	<p class="text-lg mb-6">
		Paringkelan refers to additional cyclic systems in the Balinese calendar that are used for divination, determining auspicious days, and understanding the characteristics of specific dates.
	</p>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-6">Components of Paringkelan</h2>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Jejepan</h3>
	<p class="mb-4">A system that cycles through different characteristics and is used for divination purposes.</p>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Ingkel</h3>
	<p class="mb-4">Another cyclic system used in conjunction with other paringkelan components.</p>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Watek</h3>
	<p class="mb-4">Divided into Watek Alit (small) and Watek Madya (medium), used for determining characteristics of days.</p>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Lintang</h3>
	<p class="mb-4">A system related to stars and celestial influences on daily life.</p>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Panca Suda</h3>
	<p class="mb-4">A five-fold system used for various ceremonial and divination purposes.</p>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Pararasan</h3>
	<p class="mb-4">A system with dual naming traditions (Aryana and Sundari Bungkah) used for specific calculations.</p>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Rakam</h3>
	<p class="mb-4">Another important paringkelan component used in calendar calculations.</p>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-6">Purpose and Use</h2>

	<p class="mb-6">
		Paringkelan systems are used for:
	</p>

	<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-8">
		<li>Determining auspicious and inauspicious days</li>
		<li>Divination and fortune telling</li>
		<li>Understanding personal characteristics based on birth date</li>
		<li>Planning important life events</li>
		<li>Ceremonial timing and rituals</li>
	</ul>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-6">Working with Paringkelan in Code</h2>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">use balinese_calendar::BalineseDate;

let date = BalineseDate::from_ymd(2023, 1, 1)?;

// Access various paringkelan components
println!("Jejepan: {}", date.jejepan());
println!("Ingkel: {}", date.ingkel());
println!("Watek Alit: {}", date.watek_alit());
println!("Watek Madya: {}", date.watek_madya());
println!("Lintang: {}", date.lintang());
println!("Panca Suda: {}", date.panca_suda());
println!("Pararasan: {}", date.pararasan());</code></pre>
	</div>

